The metallic skylab requires Textures Unlimited to work, and if you dont have it it will fall back to a regular stockalike texture. Also make sure you dont have anything like Magpie installed which might be applying TU configs to where its undesirable.

Also make sure your reflections are enabled in KSP settings.

reflections are on, does this link work? https://imgur.com/a/unUTZ6Z

Was going to do an Apollo mission today, but once on-orbit the S-IVB failed to ignite for transmunar injection. Had to abort, and the crew of three splashed down safely.

 

I also noticed that on the Wikipedia page for the Saturn V,  It states "For the first two uncrewed launches, eight solid-fuel ullage motors ignited for four seconds to accelerate the S-II stage, followed by the ignition of the five J-2 engines. For the first seven crewed Apollo missions only four ullage motors were used on the S-II, and they were eliminated completely for the final four launches". How did the S-II generate ullage without the motors on the interstage?

4 hours ago, zakkpaz said:

reflections are on, does this link work? https://imgur.com/a/unUTZ6Z

Alright this was caused by broken stock materials. I've pushed a fix. 

It should look like this instead of white now

However if you want the good stuff that uses the dedicated PBR textures in the subfolder you need to install Textures Unlimited (but please dont install mods like magpie which will probably try to overwrite this with its own configs). I guess most people have been using TU hence why no one has seen this issue so far.
